description:
On 10 and 11. February 202 2 WP2, Identification of practitioners&rsquo; capabilities, gaps and requirements organized a workshop in the area of Cybercrime relating to Remote Desktop Protocols and similar technologies. 
 Remote Desktop Protocol (and related technologies) became an increasing target for cybercrime both, on staff members of organisations as well as business systems through social engineering or technical means, try ing to install clients using those protocols.&nbsp; 
 Remote Desktop Protocol is a proprietary protocol developed by Microsoft. There are&nbsp;no specific standards but only on general level from ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 27 Information&nbsp;security, cybersecurity and privacy protection, CEN/CENELEC JTC 13 Cybersecurity and&nbsp;Data Protection and ETSI TC C ybersecurity&nbsp;Partners&nbsp;of Task 4.2 participated in the WP2 Workshop in the area of Cybercrime relating to&nbsp;Remote Desktop Protocols and similar technologies and collected the following needs&nbsp;expressed by practitioners. These needs were assessed regarding how these needs can be&nbsp;met by standardization.

